42 (3) 'Sex' means an individual's immutable characteristics of the reproductive system that
43 define such individual as male or female, as determined by anatomy and genetics existing
44 at the time of birth.
45 (4) 'State health plan' means any healthcare benefits provided pursuant to Subpart 2 of
46 Part 6 of Article 17 of Chapter 2 of Title 20, Subpart 3 of Part 6 of Article 17 of
47 Chapter 2 of Title 20, Code Section 31-2-4, and Article 1 of Chapter 18 of this title.
48 (5) 'Transition related intervention' means any medical procedure performed for the
49 purpose of:
50 (A) Enabling an individual to identify with or live as a purported identity inconsistent
51 with such individual's sex; or
52 (B) Treating an individual's purported discomfort or distress from a discordance
53 between such individual's sex and asserted identity.
54 (b) On or after January 1, 2026, the state health plan shall not include expenses for any
55 transition related intervention except as provided in subsection (c) of this Code section.
56 (c) The board shall adopt rules and regulations regarding the exclusion of expenses for any
57 transition related intervention as provided for in subsection (b) of this Code section;
58 provided, however, that it is not a violation of this Code section if a healthcare provider
59 performs or administers a medical procedure for the purpose of treating:
60 (1) A minor's congenital defect, precocious puberty, disease, or physical injury;
61 provided, however, that the term 'disease' does not include gender dysphoria, gender
62 identity disorder, gender incongruence, or any mental condition, disorder, disability, or
63 abnormality; and
64 (2) Any infection, injury, disease, or disorder that has been caused or exacerbated by the
65 performance of a medical procedure, including a transition related intervention, whether
66 or not such procedure was performed in accordance with federal or state law; provided,
67 however, that the purpose of such medical procedure shall not be to continue any
