69 incongruence, or any mental condition, disorder, disability, or abnormality."
70 SECTION 3.
71 Chapter 4 of Title 49 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to public assistance,
72 is amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
73 "49-4-159.5.
74 The department shall prohibit the coverage of any transition related intervention as
75 provided for in Code Section 45-18-4.2 for recipients of medical assistance."
76 SECTION 4.
77 Chapter 1 of Title 50 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to general
78 provisions relative to state government, is amended by adding a new Code section to read as
79 follows:
80 "50-1-14.
81 (a) No state funds shall be expended for health benefits coverage that includes coverage
82 for any transition related intervention as provided for in Code Section 45-18-4.2.
83 (b) No healthcare facility owned or operated by the state and no physician or other
84 healthcare provider employed by an agency or entity of this state shall provide any
85 transition related intervention as provided for in Code Section 45-18-4.2.
86 (c) No correctional facility owned or operated by the state and no physician or other
87 healthcare provider employed by such facility shall provide any transition related
88 intervention as provided for in Code Section 45-18-4.2 to any individual incarcerated at
89 such facility.
90 (d) Nothing in this Code section shall be construed as:
91 (1) Prohibiting any individual, entity, or local government from purchasing separate
92 coverage for any transition related intervention or health benefits coverage that includes
